<p id="fsta"><span class="boldpage">Allworld Corporation</span> (“<span class="boldpage">we</span>,” “<span class="boldpage">our</span>,” or “<span class="boldpage">us</span>”) values your privacy and is committed to ensuring that your personal data is handled securely and in compliance with the <span class="boldpage">Data Privacy Act of 2012 (RA No. 10173)</span> and the <span class="boldpage">National Telecommunications Commission (NTC)</span> regulations. This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your personal information when you use our services.</p>
<p>By accessing or using our website, purchasing products, or interacting with us, you consent to the practices outlined in this Privacy Policy.</p>
<p>For purposes of this Privacy Policy, "<span class="boldpage">you</span>" and "<span class="boldpage">your</span>" means you as the user of this website, whether you are a customer, website visitor, or another individual whose information we have collected pursuant to this Privacy Policy.</p>
<h3>1. Personal Data We Collect</h3>
<p>When you make a purchase, register an account, contact customer service or when we improve our service we may collect the following:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><span class="boldpage">Personal Identifiable Information (PII):</span> Includes your full name, email address, mailing address, phone number, and date of birth.</li>
        <li><span class="boldpage">Transaction Details:</span> Includes order history, payment history, and delivery information.</li>
        <li><span class="boldpage">Technical Data:</span> Includes IP address, browser type, device information, and browsing behavior on our website.</li>
        <li><span class="boldpage">Non-Personal Information:</span> We may collect data that does not directly identify you, such as your IP address, browser type, operating system, and browsing history on our website.</li>
        <li><span class="boldpage">Payment Information:</span> We use third-party payment processors to handle your transactions. We do not store credit or debit card information directly on our servers. However, we may collect billing information, including your shipping address and contact information.</li>
    </ul>
<h3>2. Purpose of Collection and Use of Personal Data</h3>
<p>We collect personal data for the following purposes:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><span class="boldpage">Order Processing and Delivery:</span>To process your purchases, ship products, and provide customer service.</li>
        <li><span class="boldpage">Account Management:</span>To create and manage your customer account, provide order updates, and process warranty or return requests.</li>
        <li><span class="boldpage">Marketing and Promotions: </span>To send you relevant marketing materials or promotional content if you have opted in.</li>
        <li><span class="boldpage">Improvement of Services:</span>To enhance our website, products, and services based on customer feedback and usage data.</li>
        <li><span class="boldpage">Compliance with Legal Obligations:</span>To comply with legal requirements, including fulfilling obligations under the Data Privacy Act and other applicable laws.</li>
    </ul>
<h3>3. Sharing of Personal Data</h3>
<p>We will not share, sell, or trade your personal data with third parties unless:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><span class="boldpage">With Service Providers:</span>We may share your information with trusted third-party service providers, such as payment processors, delivery partners, and marketing platforms, to facilitate the services they provide to us. These service providers are contractually obligated to protect your data and use it only for the services they provide to us.</li>
        <li><span class="boldpage">Legal Compliance:</span>We may disclose your personal data if required by law, regulatory authorities, or in response to a valid court order or legal process.</li>
        <li><span class="boldpage">Business Transfers:</span>In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your personal data may be transferred to the new entity, subject to the terms of this Privacy Policy.</li>
    </ul>
<h3>4. Data Subject Rights (Your Privacy Rights)</h3>
<p>Under the Data Privacy Act of 2012, you have the following rights with respect to your personal data:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><span class="boldpage">Right to Access:</span>You can request access to the personal data we hold about you.</li>
        <li><span class="boldpage">Right to Correct:</span>You can request corrections to any inaccurate or incomplete personal data.</li>
        <li><span class="boldpage">Right to Object:</span>You can object to the processing of your personal data under certain circumstances or ask us to stop or restrict our processing of personal information.</li>
        <li><span class="boldpage">Right to Erasure (Right to be Forgotten):</span>You may request the deletion of your personal data from our records, subject to certain legal exceptions.</li>
        <li><span class="boldpage">Right to Data Portability:</span>You have the right to request a copy of your personal data in a structured, commonly used, and machine-readable format.</li>
        <li><span class="boldpage">Withdrawal of Consent:</span>You may have the right to withdraw the consent to process your personal information.</li>
        <li><span class="boldpage">Appeal:</span>You may have a right to appeal our decision if we decline to process your request. You can do so by replying directly to our denial.</li>    
    </ul>
<p>We will not discriminate against you for exercising any of these rights. We may need to collect information from you to verify your identity, such as your email address or account information, before providing a substantive response to the request.</p>
<p>In accordance with applicable laws, You may designate an authorized agent to make requests on your behalf to exercise your rights. Before accepting such a request from an agent, we will require that the agent provide proof you have authorized them to act on your behalf, and we may need you to verify your identity directly with us. We will respond to your request in a timely manner as required under applicable law.</p>
<h3>5. Data Retention</h3>
<p>We retain your personal data for no longer than is necessary for the purposes stated in this Privacy Policy, or as required by applicable law. Once your personal data is no longer necessary for those purposes, we will ensure it is securely deleted or anonymized.</p>
<h3>6. Protection of Personal Data</h3>
<p>We take reasonable steps to ensure that your personal data is protected from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. This includes using encryption, secure servers, firewalls, and restricted access to sensitive data.</p>
<p>However, please be aware that no method of electronic transmission or storage is 100% secure. While we strive to protect your data, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.</p>
<h3>7. Use of Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h3>
<p>We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to improve user experience and provide personalized content. Cookies are small text files that are stored on your device when you visit our website. You can control cookie settings through your browser preferences. However, disabling cookies may affect your ability to use some features of our site.</p>
<h3>8. Children’s Privacy</h3>
<p>Our website and services are not intended for use by individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children. If we become aware that we have inadvertently collected personal data from a child under 18, we will take steps to delete it, or you may contact us using the contact details set out below to request that it be deleted.</p>
<h3>9. Third-Party Links</h3>
<p>Our website may contain links to third-party websites or services. This Privacy Policy applies only to our website, and we are not responsible for the privacy practices of external sites. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of any third-party sites you visit.</p>
<p>Our inclusion of such links does not, by itself, imply any endorsement of the content on such platforms or of their owners or operators.</p>
<h3>10. Changes to this Privacy Policy</h3>
<p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. We will notify you of any significant changes by posting the updated Privacy Policy on our website and revising the effective date. We encourage you to review this policy periodically.</p>
